title: Grateful Dead Live at Music Hall on 1973-12-01
lineage: Maxell UD90's > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > R8Brain > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged.
taper: Bill Degen. This transfer is 1st Gen cassettes, kindly provided by Tim Friend.
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Big River, Brokedown Palace, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow, Casey Jones

Set 2

Around & Around, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle, Don't Ease Me In, Me And Bobby McGee, Mississippi Half Step, Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band, Row Jimmy, Greatest Story Ever Told, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away

reviews.review_text: a little rough I spun a few cassettes of these shows from Bill Degen's reels back in the early 80's.  Maybe is was the equipment, but this sounds quite a bit better than I remember.  He had an impressive collection for the time period.  (i guess I was easily impressed by what were then the "old timers" who started seeing shows in the late 60's and early 70's)
